 the myth that the big banks are automatically strong banks has since broken by experience of failures of many big private banks worldwide including in the usa  while the sbi as a standalone entity reported a profit a rs 10484 crore for the year 201617 the new consolidated sbi after the merger  of  five  associate  banks  made  a  loss  of  rs  390  crore  for  the  same  year  there  are  no  short  cuts  to  rehabilitating  banks  except  taking  strong  measures  for the  recovery  of  sticky  loans  of  stateowned  banks  and  recapitalization  of beleaguered banks  the public sector banks have to be defended and saved    